);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = non_zero_random(-5,5,1);
$b = non_zero_random(-5,5,1);
$c = non_zero_random(-5,5,1);
$d = $a*$b + $a**2;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Suppose that \(x = x(t)\) and \(y=y(t)\) are both functions of
\(t\).  If
\[
    x^2 + xy = $d,
\]
and \(dx/dt = $c\) when \(x = $a\) and \(y = $b\), what is \(dy/dt\)?
$BR
$BR
\(dy/dt\) = \{ans_rule(20) \}
$BR

EOT

$ans = (-2*$a*$c - $b*$c)/$a;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

ENDDOCUMENT();
